---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../styles/pages/about.css';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="Laurie Di Francesco — artist-author working through photography and writing."
>

  <!-- ── Titre + Épigraphe ────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="about-head container">
    <p class="about-eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1 class="about-h1">Laurie Di Francesco</h1>

    <div class="about-epi">
      <blockquote>
        All men by nature desire to know. An indication of this is the delight we
        take in our senses; for even apart from their usefulness they are loved for
        themselves; and above all others <span class="k">the sense of sight</span>.
      </blockquote>
      <cite>Aristotle — Metaphysics, Book A</cite>
    </div>
    <hr class="horizon about-horizon" />
  </section>

  <!-- ── Bio ───────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="about-bio">

    <div class="bio-portrait">
      <img
        src="/images/about-redscarf-softened.jpg"
        alt="Laurie Di Francesco"
        loading="eager"
      />
    </div>

    <p>Laurie Di Francesco is an artist-author whose practice runs mainly through photography and writing.</p>

    <p>Raised between France and Italy, this double belonging allowed her to grasp early on <span class="k">the strength and fragility of the threshold</span>, and to question what it means to be rooted: a displacement that reaches even into the language she thinks in. <span class="k">The blue of the sky</span>, unchanging from one end of the earth to the other, is a recurring motif in her work, questioned as a possible <span class="k">anchor point to the world</span>.</p>

    <p>As a young adult, she moved to Brazil, a land of the heart and of expansion for her practice: there she took her first photography courses at twenty, in Rio de Janeiro, at Ateliê da Imagem. She then refined her technique at ENSP in Arles (France), alongside professionals such as Fabienne Pavia, Antoine d'Agata, and Klavdij Sluban.</p>

    <p>A philosophy graduate, she approaches art as an <span class="k">existentialist</span>, nourished by Nietzsche, Ricœur, and Bachelard: <span class="k">transfiguring the real without idealizing it</span>, in what it holds of light as much as fragility.</p>

    <p>She exhibited for the first time in Belo Horizonte, Brazil, in 2024: <em>Spilling Beyond the Lines</em>, built from archival images.</p>

    <p>Her work continues today through several projects: the threshold, with <em>Quando sono qui, non sono là</em>; the body's relationship to water, in the wake of <em>En corps à la mer</em>; and, with <em>Is this love that I'm feeling?</em>, love as a possible place to give birth to oneself again.</p>

    <p class="bio-inspirations">Inspirations: Claudia Andujar, Graciela Iturbide, Luigi Ghirri,
    Jacques-Henri Lartigue, Manuel Álvarez Bravo, Miguel Rio Branco, José Diniz, Letizia
    Battaglia, among others.</p>

  </div>

</Layout>
